docs.abstract: Concern is growing among businesses and lawmakers in both parties that President Trump has no clear strategy to resolve the escalating dispute.
docs.snippet: Concern is growing among businesses and lawmakers in both parties that President Trump has no clear strategy to resolve the escalating dispute.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The trade war between the United States and China showed no signs of yielding on Thursday, as Steven Mnuchin, the Treasury secretary, told lawmakers there was no clear path to resolution and Beijing blasted the administration over its approach.

headline.main: As Trade War Persists, Mnuchin Says China Talks Have ‘Broken Down’
headline.print_headline: Mnuchin, Facing Bipartisan Ire, Says China Talks Have ‘Broken Down’

byline.original: By Alan Rappeport and Jim Tankersley

docs.abstract: Jerome H. Powell said a potential trade war would have no immediate effect on the Federal Reserve’s strategy of gradually increasing interest rates.
docs.snippet: Jerome H. Powell said a potential trade war would have no immediate effect on the Federal Reserve’s strategy of gradually increasing interest rates.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Jerome H. Powell used his inaugural speech as Federal Reserve chairman on Friday to highlight the strength of the United States economic recovery, and told a questioner that a potential trade war would have no immediate effect on the Fed’s plans to continue gradually raising interest rates this year.

headline.main: Powell Touts Economy’s Strength in First Speech as Fed Chief

docs.abstract: The Trump administration also blacklisted four associates of President Nicolás Maduro, pressuring a government it has accused of graft and repression.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration also blacklisted four associates of President Nicolás Maduro, pressuring a government it has accused of graft and repression.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration announced on Monday that it was broadening sanctions against Venezuela, blacklisting four government officials and banning a digital currency President Nicolás Maduro created last month to circumvent financial sanctions on his economically strapped nation.

headline.main: White House Bans Venezuela’s Digital Currency and Expands Sanctions
headline.print_headline: White House Bans Venezuela’s Digital Currency and Imposes Further Sanctions

byline.original: By Julie Hirschfeld Davis and Nathaniel Popper

docs.abstract: In an interview on “Fox & Friends,” the president said that the investigation of his lawyer, Michael Cohen, was about Mr. Cohen’s personal business dealings.
docs.snippet: In an interview on “Fox & Friends,” the president said that the investigation of his lawyer, Michael Cohen, was about Mr. Cohen’s personal business dealings.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump distanced himself from his longtime lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, on Thursday, saying that a federal criminal investigation was focused on Mr. Cohen’s business dealings and had nothing to do with his legal representation of the president.

headline.main: Trump Distances Himself From Cohen’s Legal Troubles
headline.print_headline: Trump Distances Himself From Cohen Inquiry

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, confronting legal threats on multiple sides, sought on Wednesday to discredit a pornographic actress alleging a sexual encounter with him and investigators examining whether his campaign worked with Russia to sway the 2016 election, saying both were dealing in fake allegations.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats said on Friday that they would seek to ensure that continuing budget negotiations included legislation to protect Robert S. Mueller III, the special counsel in the Russia investigation, from being fired by President Trump.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — He assailed the “scum on top” of the F.B.I. who were out to get him. He suggested that a former aide did not lie even though he pleaded guilty to lying to investigators. And he distanced himself from his onetime campaign chairman hours before the aide was sent to jail.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump made his first “Crooked Hillary” Twitter post less than 48 hours into the new year on Tuesday, accusing a former Clinton aide of “disregarding basic security protocols,” and calling his own Justice Department a “deep state.”

headline.main: Trump Accuses Former Clinton Aide of Failing to Follow Security Protocols

docs.abstract: Republicans and Democrats are in the middle of a legislative battle over the program created by President Barack Obama, called the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals, or DACA.
docs.snippet: Republicans and Democrats are in the middle of a legislative battle over the program created by President Barack Obama, called the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals, or DACA.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump called the United States courts system “broken and unfair” on Wednesday, the morning after a federal judge’s ruling that ordered the administration to restart a program that shields young, undocumented immigrants from deportation.

headline.main: ‘Outrageous,’ White House Says of DACA Ruling, as Trump Calls Court System ‘Broken’

docs.abstract: As prosecutors revealed a monthslong fraud investigation of Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s personal lawyer and fixer, Mr. Trump called Mr. Cohen on Friday to “check in.”
docs.snippet: As prosecutors revealed a monthslong fraud investigation of Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s personal lawyer and fixer, Mr. Trump called Mr. Cohen on Friday to “check in.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s advisers have concluded that a wide-ranging corruption investigation into his personal lawyer poses a greater and more imminent threat to the president than even the special counsel’s investigation, according to several people close to Mr. Trump.

headline.main: Trump Sees Inquiry Into Cohen as Greater Threat Than Mueller
headline.print_headline: Lawyer’s Files  A Bigger Risk  Than Mueller
